==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Flying lemur
<hw>Fly"ing le"mur</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>either of
two nocturnal lemurlike mammals inhabiting the East Indies
(<spn>Cynocephalus variegatus</spn>) or the Phillipines
(<spn>Cynocephalus volans</spn>) having broad folds of skin between the
fore and hind limbs on both sides of the body allowing them to make long
gliding leaps; they have been classed in the separate order
<ord>Dermoptera</ord>. They are arboreal and have become rare.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flying squirrel</ent>⟦br⟧
